  "body": "<!-- **Are you in the right place?**\r\n1. For issues or feature requests, please create an issue in this repository.\r\n2. For general technical and non-technical questions, we are happy to help you on our [Rook.io Slack](https://Rook-io.slack.com).\r\n3. Did you already search the existing open issues for anything similar? -->\r\n\r\n**Is this a bug report or feature request?**\r\n* Feature Request\r\n\r\n**What should the feature do:**\r\n\r\nFor performance vs. availability tradeoffs, EdgeFS allows flexible selection of sync operation. We need to provide a way to change it via cluster CRD. Example:\r\n\r\n```yaml\r\n...\r\n  storage:\r\n    config:\r\n      sync: 3\r\n...\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis has to be cluster  or node scope option. Default is 1, i.e. consistent in case of software crash or power loss.\r\n\r\n**What is use case behind this feature:**\r\n\r\nTo allow users flexibility they need during deployment. If they need absolutely durable storage, sync has to be set to 3. If they want consistency with reduced durability, it can be 2 or 1. If they need scratch-pad performance, sync can be set to 0.\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n<!-- Specific environment information that helps with the feature request -->\r\n",
